@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@adminToken = REPLACE_WITH_JWT_FROM_ADMIN_USER
@itemId = 00000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001
@claimId = 00000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000002
@userId = 00000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000003

### All admin routes are under /admin. Use GET/PUT/DELETE in UPPERCASE (not "Get").
### If you add @Roles(ADMIN) on AdminController, use a user with role ADMIN here.

### Dashboard
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/dashboard
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Pending items queue
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/pending-items
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Approve item (UUID in path)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/admin/items/{{itemId}}/approve
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "APPROVED",
  "adminMessage": "Looks valid"
}

### Reject item
PUT {{baseUrl}}/admin/items/{{itemId}}/reject
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "REJECTED",
  "adminMessage": "Not enough detail"
}

### Pending claims
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/pending-claims
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Approve claim
PUT {{baseUrl}}/admin/claims/{{claimId}}/approve
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "APPROVED"
}

### Reject claim
PUT {{baseUrl}}/admin/claims/{{claimId}}/reject
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "REJECTED",
  "adminMessage": "Evidence insufficient"
}

### List users
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Delete user
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/admin/users/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
